This repository is independent and is not endorsed, certified, sponsored, or approved by HL7.

References to FHIR are made only for conceptual comparison and attribution. This project may be described as “FHIR-informed” or “informed by selected FHIR concepts,” but it must not be described as an official FHIR implementation, FHIR Implementation Guide, FHIR profile, FHIR derivative standard, “FHIR Lite,” or a non-medical edition of FHIR.

## FHIR relationship statement

This project is not an implementation of HL7 FHIR.

It selectively references mature FHIR concepts such as logical identity, versioned reference, human-readable narrative, controlled coding, and provenance-style auditability. These concepts are adapted into a non-medical static publishing governance context.

The contribution of this project is the governance composition: stable logical identity, content-derived CID snapshots, public-safe projection, source-reference metadata, registry policy, release-gate verification, inventory guarding, and governance-oriented changelog practice.

## Excluded content

Organization-specific content, third-party media, press images, private registries, credentials, account recovery flows, secrets, internal governance logs, production deployment data, and project-specific implementation records are excluded from this repository and are not licensed here.

Unless explicitly included in this repository and covered by a license statement, such excluded materials remain outside the scope of this open reference release.

